title: Prisoner Deal Could Smooth Effort to Contain Iran’s Nuclear Program
description: Iran and the United States appear to be observing an informal agreement under which Iran has limited its nuclear program and restrained proxy militias.

title: Ecuador Reels From Assassination of Fernando Villavicencio
description: The killing of Fernando Villavicencio marks a grim turning point for a once-tranquil country now awash in violence fueled by drug gangs.

title: Russia Tries to Bolster Ruble as Inflation Adds to Economic Woes
description: The central bank in Moscow took steps to counter the currency’s slide, but the war and resulting sanctions have put intense pressure on the economy.

title: What Happened to Britain’s ‘Crooked House’ Pub?
description: The beloved tilted landmark in the West Midlands area of England was razed after a fire that police suspect was arson, leaving locals looking for answers.

title: Biden Seeks Another $24 Billion for Ukraine in Test of Bipartisan Support
description: The aid request is the first by the president since Republicans took over the House in January, and some party leaders have expressed opposition to spending more to help Ukraine beat back Russian forces.

title: Yandex Founder Calls Russia’s War In Ukraine ‘Barbaric’
description: Arkady Volozh is only the second sanctioned Russian businessman to take an unequivocal public position against the invasion.

title: U.S. Reaches Deal With Iran to Free Americans for Jailed Iranians and Funds
description: Five American detainees will eventually be allowed to leave Iran in exchange for Tehran gaining access to $6 billion for humanitarian purposes and the United States freeing several jailed Iranians.

title: Italy’s Government Takes Aim at Taxi Shortages
description: The government took steps this week to increase the supply of cabs after months of shortages, but critics say the problems with the industry run deeper.

title: Sweden Is Not Staying Neutral in Russia’s Information War
description: The country has empowered a government agency to openly combat online disinformation coming from foreign adversaries, and especially the Kremlin.

title: Muon Discovery Moves Physicists One Step Closer to a Theoretical Showdown
description: The deviance of a tiny particle called the muon might prove that one of the most well-tested theories in physics is incomplete.

title: Russia Is Making Copies of Iranian Drones to Attack Ukraine
description: Called the Geran-2, the drones are a Russian-made version of the Shahed-136, which explodes on impact, researchers say.

title: The ruble’s fall is raising concerns inside Russia about future financial shocks.
description: The Russian currency has lost about a quarter of its value this year, a reflection of the country’s roiling economy.

title: Few Options on Niger Crisis for West African Leaders
description: Niger’s new military leaders named a new government hours before West Africa’s heads of state were scheduled to decide on their response to the coup.

title: Russia-Ukraine War: Drones Target Moscow Region for Sixth Time This Month
description: Moscow blamed Ukraine for the latest attack, as the pace of strikes deep inside Russia has appeared to pick up.

title: A Drone’s View Behind Russian Lines: Cratered Fields and Charred Armor
description: A Ukrainian unit sent a drone into Russian-occupied territory to surveil the battlefront, and it brought back vivid images of the Russian side of the war zone.

title: Israel’s Supreme Court Braces to Rule on Judicial Overhaul
description: The justices will be scrutinized as never before at a hearing in September on the first part of a judicial overhaul that the government pushed through Parliament, angering many Israelis.

title: What to Know About Fernando Villavicencio, Who Was Assassinated in Ecuador
description: The presidential candidate who was assassinated on Wednesday had a long history in Ecuador’s public affairs, largely as an antagonist to those in power.

title: 4 Nigerian Migrants Crossed the Atlantic on a Ship’s Rudder to Brazil
description: Four Nigerian stowaways hopped on a cargo ship not knowing where it was going, but hoping to find a place where they could claw out of poverty.

title: Ecuador Presidential Candidate Is Assassinated During Rally
description: The candidate, Fernando Villavicencio, was outspoken about the link between organized crime and government officials.

title: Typhoon Khanun Lands in South Korea
description: After pummeling southern Japan, killing two people, the storm is expected to move slowly across the Korean Peninsula, bringing heavy rain and wind.
